<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="759" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                            <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Motley</persName></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 185.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-05-26"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 26, 1866.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your despatch of the 8th instant, No. 170, which paper is
                                accompanied by a copy of a note which, on the 6th instant, you
                                addressed to Count Mensdorff in execution of my instructions Nos.
                                173, 174, and 176.</p>
                            <p>I have great pleasure in saying that the President approves entirely
                                of the proceedings on your part which are related in your despatch,
                                and equally approves of your note to the Austrian minister for
                                foreign affairs.</p>
                            <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">J. Lothrop Motley</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Vienna</hi>.</p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>